org.midao.jdbc.core.handlers.output.lazy

Interface LazyScrollOutputHandler<T,S>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    LazyOutputHandler<T,S>, OutputHandler<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LazyScrollUpdateOutputHandler<T,S>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BeanLazyScrollOutputHandler, BeanLazyScrollUpdateOutputHandler, MapLazyScrollOutputHandler, MapLazyScrollUpdateOutputHandler

    public interface LazyScrollOutputHandler<T,S>
extends LazyOutputHandler<T,S>
    Lazy scrollable output handler handles output from LazyStatementHandler and allows lazy loading of data from it.

    If underlying JDBC Driver doesn't support scrollable ResultSet - exception would be thrown. In order to check if JDBC Driver supports such functionality - please read relevant JDBC driver documentation and/or create POC (Proof of concept).

    Scroll supports only one ResultSet due to the fact that some JDBC Drivers close previous ResultSet before returning next one. In cases where multiple ResultSets need to be handled - please use cached or standard(non-scrollable) lazy output.
